  "body": "Hello:\n\nI'm following along with the docs adding transitions via  `ReactCSSTransitionGroup = React.addons.CSSTransitionGroup` and everything is working great. The only problem I have is that the transition fires even on the mount of the component, despite what the docs say, and nothing I do will turn it off. Here's my component:\n\n```\nC.FeedList = React.createClass({\n    render() {\n        return (\n            <div>\n            <C.ReactCSSTransitionGroup transitionName=\"feed-transition\">\n        {\n          this.props.posts.map(doc => {\n            return <C.PostItem key={doc._id}\n              { ...doc }\n              destroyPost={ doc.destroy }/>;\n          })\n        }\n            </C.ReactCSSTransitionGroup>\n      </div>\n        );\n    }\n});\n```\n\nWhat am I doing wrong?\n",
